%% Reviewed 2026-03-26 for B-001 to keep Odylith product topology and governance diagrams canonical in the public Atlas catalog.
flowchart LR
  Tribunal["Tribunal outcome<br/>case brief, systemic brief, proof refs,<br/>confidence, next discriminating check"]
  Packet["Remediator packet<br/>Approve and apply / Send to AI engine / Review manually"]

  subgraph Inbox["Shell + Odylith"]
    Shell["Tooling shell<br/>Operator inbox preview<br/>top ranked cases + terse warnings"]
    Odylith["Odylith workspace<br/>ranked cases, selected brief, proof, action buttons,<br/>approval and clearance state"]
  end

  subgraph Evidence["Native Evidence Surfaces"]
    Radar["Radar<br/>workstream evidence,<br/>traceability, and topology"]
    Registry["Registry<br/>component authority,<br/>forensics, and ownership evidence"]
    Casebook["Casebook<br/>bug history,<br/>root cause, and prevention evidence"]
    Atlas["Atlas<br/>diagram freshness,<br/>topology, and linked artifacts"]
    Compass["Compass<br/>timeline evidence,<br/>recent changes, and checkpoints"]
  end

  Tribunal --> Shell
  Tribunal --> Odylith
  Packet --> Odylith

  Shell -->|Open full case| Odylith
  Odylith -->|Open proof| Radar
